## V4-Specific Rules

19. **Control Layer is architectural, not a feature.** It sits between the Application Layer and the AI Layer. Every feature that enforces rules, requires approvals, tracks SLAs, or handles exceptions routes through the Control Layer — not through individual feature code. Build it as a shared service, not per-feature logic.
20. **Approvals are blocking by default.** When an approval is required, the action is BLOCKED until approved. No "soft" approvals that just log but don't enforce. Override is possible but requires documented reason + audit trail.
21. **SLA timers are real-time.** Not computed on page load — they tick in the background. A cron job checks SLA breaches every 5 minutes and triggers escalation actions.
22. **Workflow versioning is Git-like.** Draft → Active → Archived. Only one version active at a time. Rollback creates a new version from the old one (doesn't delete history).
23. **Exception handling requires approval chain.** Overriding any rule or SLA is itself an action that may require approval (configurable per org). The exception is logged with: who, what rule was overridden, why (free text), approved by whom.
24. **Handoff notes are mandatory and enforced.** The system blocks deal/account reassignment without handoff notes. The UI disables the "Reassign" action until notes are written. No backdoor.
25. **Observability is admin-only.** The operations dashboard is visible only to Owner and Admin roles. Not Manager, not Executive.
26. **Marketing intelligence profiles are append-only.** The contact behavioral profile logs every data point — never overwrites. Historical patterns are preserved. The AI reads the full history to detect trends.
27. **Campaign approval is atomic.** When a user approves a batch campaign, the entire batch is committed. No partial approval (approve some messages, reject others). If adjustments needed, user modifies the plan and re-approves.
28. **AI explainability is mandatory on all insights.** Every AI-generated insight, score, recommendation, or campaign suggestion must include: what inputs were used, what the confidence level is, and a plain-language explanation of reasoning. This is enforced at the orchestrator validation layer.
29. **Forecasting labeled as "projection."** All AI-generated revenue predictions must be labeled "Projection" not "Forecast" unless historical accuracy has been proven (>80% accuracy over 3+ periods). This is a display rule, not a technical constraint.

